flowchart TB
  contributor["Contributor or agent"]:::person
  reviewer["Reviewer or maintainer"]:::person
  execution["Local shell and GitHub Actions<br/>[Validation execution]"]:::external
  package_runner["npm/npx package runner<br/>[CLI delivery surface]"]:::external
  npm_registry["npm registry<br/>[Public package registry]"]:::external
  adapter_user["Codex, Claude Code, and opencode user"]:::person

  subgraph repo["RigorLoop repository<br/>[Git repository]"]
    governance["Governance and workflow guidance<br/>[Markdown]"]:::container
    lifecycle["Lifecycle artifacts and ADRs<br/>[Markdown and YAML]"]:::container
    token_bench["Token-cost benchmark fixtures and reports<br/>[Markdown, YAML, JSONL]"]:::container
    cli["RigorLoop CLI package<br/>[Node/npm package]"]:::container
    architecture["Canonical architecture package<br/>[Markdown and Mermaid]"]:::container
    changes["Change-local evidence<br/>[Markdown and YAML]"]:::container
    validation_cache["Local validation execution cache<br/>[Untracked local state]"]:::container
    templates["Templates and diagram styles<br/>[Markdown and Mermaid]"]:::container
    skills["Canonical skills and adapter templates<br/>[Markdown and templates]"]:::container
    scripts["Validation and generation scripts<br/>[Python and shell]"]:::container
    generated["Generated runtime mirrors and adapters<br/>[Generated Markdown, metadata, commands, and release archives]"]:::container
    release["Release evidence<br/>[YAML, Markdown, checksums, smoke evidence]"]:::container
    legacy["Legacy architecture archive<br/>[Archived Markdown]"]:::container
  end

  contributor -->|records workflow intent, manual-skill isolation, and no-impact rationale in| lifecycle
  contributor -->|updates clear current architecture truth directly in| architecture
  contributor -->|uses for historical, review, validation, and exceptional evidence in| changes
  contributor -->|authors benchmark prompts, fixtures, reports, and metadata in| token_bench
  contributor -->|runs help, version, multi-adapter init, and new-change through| cli
  contributor -->|uses scaffolds from| templates
  contributor -->|edits canonical sources in| skills
  reviewer -->|reviews selected architecture surface and ADR need in| architecture
  reviewer -->|reviews change-local reasoning and closeout when present in| changes
  governance -->|defines one standard workflow, manual-skill isolation, and source-of-truth rules for| lifecycle
  governance -->|defines lowest-sufficient architecture-surface rules for| architecture
  governance -->|declares authored/generated boundaries for| skills
  lifecycle -->|routes architecture work to no-impact rationale, direct update, ADR, or proposal/spec gap| architecture
  changes -->|may expose durable truth that must be represented in| architecture
  changes -->|record reviews, explanations, validation gaps, and final closeout evidence for| lifecycle
  templates -->|scaffold architecture and ADR records in| lifecycle
  skills -->|are transformed by| scripts
  scripts -->|generate temp output, tracked adapter output, and release artifacts for| generated
  scripts -->|runs benchmarks, analyzes JSONL, and validates metadata for| token_bench
  cli -->|uses bundled official adapter metadata, adapter descriptors, and small scaffolds from| release
  cli -->|writes safe project/change scaffolds, records schema v2 lockfile state, and installs verified adapter output from| generated
  cli -->|is executed by| package_runner
  cli -->|is published after package-content, smoke, and publication-mode checks to| npm_registry
  npm_registry -->|delivers the published package to| package_runner
  generated -->|provides public Codex skills for benchmark temp fixtures used by| token_bench
  scripts -->|validate lifecycle, metadata, review artifacts, release data, and drift for| lifecycle
  scripts -->|route registered evidence and query bounded change-record slices in| changes
  scripts -->|read and write non-portable cache entries in| validation_cache
  validation_cache -->|may produce reviewable cache-hit claims recorded in| changes
  scripts -->|run in| execution
  release -->|records metadata and checksums for publication of| generated
  release -->|links token-friendliness report evidence from| token_bench
  generated -->|is consumed by| adapter_user
  legacy -->|preserves historical evidence after accepted current content reaches| architecture
  architecture -->|summarizes and links ADRs in| lifecycle

  classDef person fill:#08427b,stroke:#073b6f,color:#fff
  classDef system fill:#1168bd,stroke:#0e5aa7,color:#fff
  classDef external fill:#999,stroke:#666,color:#fff
  classDef container fill:#438dd5,stroke:#3c7fc0,color:#fff
